{{Infobox school| caption =International School of Almaty | city = Satpayev, 40B | state = [[Almaty, Kazakhstan|Almaty]] | zipcode = 050006 | country = [[Kazakhstan]] | type = Private | established = 2000 | director = Akasheva Zhibek Zekenovna | nickname = ISA | website = {{URL|https://www.qsi.org/kazakhstan/kaz/}} }} The '''International School of Almaty (ISA)''' in [[Kazakhstan]] is a branch of the "Education Fund of Nursultan Nazarbayev".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.qsi.org/kazakhstan/kaz/|title=Almaty International School |publisher=Quality Schools International}}</ref> The school provides education on integrated programs of the state educational standard of the Republic of Kazakhstan and the International Baccalaureate of primary and basic schools from the 1st to the 11th grade.
In 2017 the school was admitted to the UNESCO Associated Schools.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aspnet.unesco.org/en-us/Lists/Schools/PublicDispForm.aspx?ID=93085|publisher=UNESCO Associated Schools Project Network|title=International School of Almaty}}</ref> The International School of Almaty hosts an annual contest of social and creative projects of UNESCO Associated Schools.
==Administration== {{unsourced section|date=March 2018}} The director of the International School of Almaty is Akasheva Zhibek Zekenovna, a Honored Worker of Education of the Republic of Kazakhstan, laureate of Tarlan Prize. The coordinator of international programs is Bazarbayeva Roza Kasymovna.
==History== In 2000, the school became the first in Kazakhstan to be authorized by the International Baccalaureate Organization for the Middle Years Program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibo.org/en/school/001828|publisher=International Baccalaureate|title=International School of Almaty of Nazarbaev Educational Fund}}</ref> In 2013, the school was authorized for the [[Primary Years Programme|Primary Years Program]], an elementary school program. Since 2009, the school has been certified as a member of the Cambridge Educational Group.{{cn|date=March 2018}}
