'''Professor Paul Rowlett''' is a specialist in [[French language|French]] linguistics and was the last head of the School of Humanities, Languages and Social Sciences at [[Salford University]].<ref name=Salford>{{cite web|title=Paul Rowlett|url=https://salford.academia.edu/PaulRowlett|work=Academia.edu|publisher=[[University of Salford]]|accessdate=15 May 2011}}</ref> He is also the editor of the [[Philological Society]]'s peer-reviewed linguistics journal ''[[Transactions of the Philological Society]]'' and a member of the editorial board of the ''[[Journal of French Language Studies]]''.<ref name=Salford/> He is the author of three books: ''The Syntax of French'' (2007), ''The French Language Today: A Linguistic Introduction'' (2000) and ''Sentential Negation in French'' (1998).

