'''St. Theresa's Medical University of Yerevan''' (also known as '''St. Theresa Charitable Sisters Medical Institute''') is a [[private school|private]] [[medical school]] in Yerevan, Armenia, established in 1992. It is ranked #1 among private medical schools in Armenia.

The University collaborates with medical universities in the [[Medical school in the United States|USA]], Netherlands, Italy, Thailand, and [[Medical school in Canada|Canada]] through the [[World Health Organization]]. It is the only institute in Armenia that participates in the international market of [[physician]] placement.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stmu.am |title=Home - St. Tereza Medical University}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.expo.am/armenia/doc/sp/teresa.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110531154237/http://www.expo.am/armenia/doc/sp/teresa.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2011-05-31 |title=The Medical University after St.Theresa }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=11107&page=67 |title=Higher Educational Institutions in Armenia |work=Science and Technology in Armenia: Toward a Knowledge-Based Economy |year=2004 |page=67}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aid.am/pagesite.php?s=191 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130627093149/http://www.aid.am/pagesite.php?s=191 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-06-27 |title=Medical University Named After Saint Teresa }}</ref>

Graduates of St. Theresa's possess certified [[Medical specialist|specialist]] qualifications. 

